#: ../source/release-notes/2.2.txt:467
msgid "``mongooplog`` for Replaying Oplogs"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.2.txt:469
msgid ""
"The ``mongooplog`` tool makes it possible to pull :term:`oplog` entries "
"from :binary:`~bin.mongod` instance and apply them to another "
":binary:`~bin.mongod` instance. You can use ``mongooplog`` to achieve "
"point-in-time backup of a MongoDB data set. See the :issue:`SERVER-3873` "
"case and the ``mongooplog`` reference."
msgstr ""

